      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis-relevant shear stress quantities must be below 5% across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement performed with refinement ratio r=1.3. GCI for area-averaged wall shear stress: 1.8% (coarse-medium), 0.9% (medium-fine). GCI for volume-averaged scalar shear stress: 2.1% (coarse-medium), 1.1% (medium-fine). All values below 5% threshold; achieves Gradation 3 due to formal GCI documentation with asymptotic range confirmation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
