      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed via power-law hemolysis model integrating scalar shear stress and exposure time along Lagrangian particle trajectories. NIH directly maps to the RH < 1 acceptance criterion used for 510(k) hemolysis comparative assessment. QoI relevance confirmed by clinical consultant review."
